<!-- ============================== 6. DETAILED ANALYSIS ============================== -->
<h2 id="detailed-analysis">6. Detailed Analysis</h2>

<!-- --- Package Upgrades --- -->
<details id="pkg-upgrades">
  <summary>6.1 Package Upgrades <span class="winner-chip">semver/goose</span></summary>
  <div class="detail-body">
    <h4>What changed in PF6</h4>
    <p>PatternFly 6 requires updating all <code>@patternfly/*</code> packages to v6-compatible versions. The <code>react-charts</code> package moved to v8.x with new peer dependencies (<code>echarts</code>, <code>victory-*</code> subpackages). New packages like <code>@patternfly/react-drag-drop</code> were introduced for drag-and-drop functionality previously bundled in core.</p>

    <div class="cmp-row">
      <div class="cmp-cell">
        <h4 style="color:var(--red);">pf-codemods — No changes</h4>
        <p><code>package.json</code> is <strong>identical to main</strong>. No version bumps, no new dependencies. This branch relies on the fact that main already has PF6 package versions.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="cmp-cell">
        <h4 style="color:var(--green);">semver/goose — Updated</h4>
        <pre><code>@patternfly/react-charts: ~8.4.0 → ^8.5.1
@patternfly/react-drag-drop: ^6.0.0 (NEW)
@openshift-console/dynamic-plugin-sdk: 4.20.0 → ^4.21.0
victory-*: ^37.3.2 → ^37.3.6 (15 packages)
echarts: ^5.6.0 || ^6.0.0 (NEW)
victory-cursor-container: ^37.3.6 (NEW)
victory-zoom-container: ^37.3.6 (NEW)</code></pre>
        <p style="color:var(--red);"><strong>⚠️ Issues:</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li><code>react-helmet</code>: <strong>^6.1.0 → ^3.3.2</strong> — Major version <em>downgrade</em>. Destructive bug.</li>
          <li><code>@types/react</code>: <strong>^17.0.37 → ^18.3.0</strong> — Type mismatch with React 17 runtime.</li>
          <li><code>react</code>/<code>react-dom</code>: Pinned <code>17.0.2</code> → Range <code>^17.0.1</code> — Pin loosened.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p><strong>Verdict:</strong> semver/goose correctly adds missing PF6 peer dependencies (echarts, drag-drop, victory subpackages) that may be required for full PF6 chart functionality. However, the react-helmet downgrade and types/react mismatch are significant bugs. <span class="badge badge-green">semver/goose</span> still wins on net migration value despite the bugs.</p>
  </div>
</details>

<!-- --- Modal Migration --- -->
<details id="modal-migration">
  <summary>6.2 Modal Deprecation <span class="winner-chip">pf-codemods</span></summary>
  <div class="detail-body">
    <h4>What changed in PF6</h4>
    <p>In PF6, the old <code>Modal</code> component (which used a single-component API) was moved to <code>@patternfly/react-core/deprecated</code>. The new composable Modal pattern (<code>ModalHeader</code>, <code>ModalBody</code>, <code>ModalFooter</code>) is the primary API in <code>@patternfly/react-core</code>.</p>
    <p><strong>Required change:</strong> <code>import { Modal, ModalVariant } from '@patternfly/react-core'</code> → <code>import { Modal, ModalVariant } from '@patternfly/react-core/deprecated'</code></p>

    <div class="cmp-row">
      <div class="cmp-cell">
        <h4 style="color:var(--green);">pf-codemods — ✅ Correctly migrated (5 files)</h4>
        <pre><code>// Before (main):
import { Modal, ModalVariant, ModalBody, ... } from '@patternfly/react-core';

// After (pf-codemods):
import { ModalBody, ModalFooter, ModalHeader } from '@patternfly/react-core';
import { Modal, ModalVariant } from '@patternfly/react-core/deprecated';</code></pre>
        <p>Files: BaseModal.tsx, ConfirmModal.tsx, PodSelectorModal.tsx, CreateProjectModal.tsx, UserDefinedNetworkCreateModal.tsx</p>
      </div>
      <div class="cmp-cell">
        <h4 style="color:var(--red);">semver/goose — ❌ Not migrated</h4>
        <pre><code>// Still on semver/goose:
import { Modal, ModalVariant, ModalBody, ... } from '@patternfly/react-core';

// Modal and ModalVariant NOT moved to /deprecated</code></pre>
        <p>All 5 Modal files remain unchanged — <code>Modal</code> and <code>ModalVariant</code> are still imported from the main <code>@patternfly/react-core</code> path.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p><strong>Impact:</strong> While the build succeeds (PF6 re-exports deprecated components from main path with warnings), this is explicitly flagged in the PF6 upgrade guide and will generate console deprecation warnings at runtime. Official guidance says to use the <code>/deprecated</code> path as an intermediate step before fully migrating to the composable Modal API.</p>
  </div>
</details>

<!-- --- PageSection --- -->
<details id="pagesection-migration">
  <summary>6.3 PageSection hasBodyWrapper <span class="winner-chip">pf-codemods</span></summary>
  <div class="detail-body">
    <h4>What changed in PF6</h4>
    <p>In PF6, <code>&lt;PageSection&gt;</code> and <code>&lt;PageBreadcrumb&gt;</code> now default to wrapping their content in a <code>&lt;div&gt;</code> body wrapper. To preserve PF5 behavior (no wrapper div), you must add <code>hasBodyWrapper={false}</code>.</p>

    <div class="cmp-row">
      <div class="cmp-cell">
        <h4 style="color:var(--green);">pf-codemods — ✅ Comprehensive (24 instances, 21 files)</h4>
        <pre><code>// Before:
&lt;PageSection&gt;
  {content}
&lt;/PageSection&gt;

// After:
&lt;PageSection hasBodyWrapper={false}&gt;
  {content}
&lt;/PageSection&gt;</code></pre>
        <p>Applied consistently to every <code>&lt;PageSection&gt;</code> and <code>&lt;PageBreadcrumb&gt;</code> in the codebase.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="cmp-cell">
        <h4 style="color:var(--red);">semver/goose — ❌ Not addressed</h4>
        <p>Zero <code>hasBodyWrapper={false}</code> additions. The branch instead <em>removed</em> <code>&lt;PageSection&gt;</code> entirely from 2 form files (NetworkAttachmentDefinitionForm.tsx, UserDefinedNetworkForm.tsx), which changes the layout rather than preserving it.</p>
        <p><strong>~22 PageSection instances remain without hasBodyWrapper</strong>, meaning they will render with an extra wrapper div in PF6, potentially breaking CSS targeting and layout.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</details>

<!-- --- CSS Tokens --- -->
<details id="css-tokens">
  <summary>6.4 CSS Token Migration (pf-v5→pf-v6) <span class="winner-chip">semver/goose</span></summary>
  <div class="detail-body">
    <h4>What changed in PF6</h4>
    <p>PF6 introduced a new design token system. CSS variable prefixes changed:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Component tokens: <code>--pf-v5-c-*</code> → <code>--pf-v6-c-*</code></li>
      <li>Global tokens: <code>--pf-v5-global--*</code> → <code>--pf-t--global--*</code> (new "t" theme token format)</li>
      <li>CSS class names: <code>.pf-v5-*</code> → <code>.pf-v6-*</code></li>
      <li>Chart tokens: <code>--pf-v5-chart-*</code> → <code>--pf-v6-chart-*</code></li>
    </ul>

    <div class="cmp-row">
      <div class="cmp-cell">
        <h4 style="color:var(--red);">pf-codemods — ❌ Zero CSS migration</h4>
        <p><strong>482 <code>pf-v5</code> references remain</strong> across 2 files:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><code>tree-view.css</code>: 480 refs (vendored PF5 CSS)</li>
          <li><code>themes.ts</code>: 2 refs (chart theme variables)</li>
        </ul>
        <p>These will reference non-existent CSS variables in PF6, causing visual breakage for the tree-view component and chart styling.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="cmp-cell">
        <h4 style="color:var(--green);">semver/goose — ✅ Complete CSS migration</h4>
        <p><strong>All 482 <code>pf-v5</code> references eliminated:</strong></p>
        <pre><code>/* tree-view.css: 480 variable renames */
--pf-v5-c-tree-view--* → --pf-v6-c-tree-view--*
--pf-v5-global--spacer--sm → --pf-t--global--spacer--sm
--pf-v5-global--Color--100 → --pf-t--global--Color--100
/* ... ~200 unique variable mappings */

/* themes.ts: 2 renames */
--pf-v5-chart-global--FontFamily → --pf-v6-chart-global--FontFamily
--pf-v5-chart-global--letter-spacing → --pf-v6-chart-global--letter-spacing</code></pre>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p><strong>Impact:</strong> This is one of the most impactful migration areas. Without CSS token migration, components using the vendored tree-view CSS will lose all styling in PF6. This is a critical gap in the pf-codemods branch.</p>
  </div>
</details>

<!-- --- PopperProps --- -->
<details id="popper-props">
  <summary>6.5 PopperProps / appendTo Migration <span class="winner-chip">semver/goose</span></summary>
  <div class="detail-body">
    <h4>What changed in PF6</h4>
    <p>In PF6, Popper-based components (Dropdown, Select, Popover, Tooltip) changed their positioning API. The <code>enableFlip</code> and <code>position</code> props in <code>popperProps</code> were replaced with <code>placement</code>. Additionally, <code>appendTo="inline"</code> became the recommended pattern for portaling behavior in plugin environments.</p>

    <div class="cmp-row">
      <div class="cmp-cell">
        <h4 style="color:var(--red);">pf-codemods — ❌ Not addressed</h4>
        <p>The old <code>popperProps={{ enableFlip: true, position: 'right' }}</code> in ActionsDropdown.tsx remains unchanged. No <code>appendTo</code> additions anywhere.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="cmp-cell">
        <h4 style="color:var(--green);">semver/goose — ✅ Comprehensive</h4>
        <p>12+ instances across 9 files:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><code>Popover</code>: <code>appendTo="inline"</code> in 6 files</li>
          <li><code>Tooltip</code>: <code>appendTo="inline"</code> in 2 files</li>
          <li><code>Select</code>: <code>popperProps={{ appendTo: 'inline' }}</code> in 4 files</li>
          <li><code>Dropdown</code>: <code>popperProps</code> updated in 2 files</li>
        </ul>
        <p>⚠️ Minor issue: <code>'inline' as unknown as HTMLElement</code> type cast in NetworkPolicyAddPeerDropDown.tsx is a code smell.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</details>

<!-- --- Button icon --- -->
<details id="button-icon">
  <summary>6.6 Button Icon Prop <span class="winner-chip">semver/goose</span></summary>
  <div class="detail-body">
    <h4>What changed in PF6</h4>
    <p>In PF6, Button icons should be passed via the <code>icon</code> prop rather than as children alongside text. This is required for proper icon alignment and spacing.</p>

    <div class="cmp-row">
      <div class="cmp-cell">
        <h4 style="color:var(--red);">pf-codemods — ❌ Not addressed</h4>
        <p>No Button icon prop migrations.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="cmp-cell">
        <h4 style="color:var(--green);">semver/goose — ✅ Migrated (2 files)</h4>
        <pre><code>// TLSSettings.tsx - Before:
&lt;Button variant={ButtonVariant.link}&gt;
  &lt;EyeIcon /&gt; {t('Reveal')}
&lt;/Button&gt;

// After:
&lt;Button icon={&lt;EyeIcon /&gt;} variant={ButtonVariant.link}&gt;
  {t('Reveal')}
&lt;/Button&gt;</code></pre>
        <p>⚠️ PodStatus.tsx: <code>&lt;Status&gt;</code> moved to <code>icon</code> prop but button text was removed, making it icon-only. Possible accessibility concern.</p>
      </div>
