<!-- --- ListItem --- -->
<details id="listitem-icon">
  <summary>6.11 ListItem icon Prop <span class="winner-chip">semver/goose</span></summary>
  <div class="detail-body">
    <h4>What changed in PF6</h4>
    <p>In PF6, <code>ListItem</code> uses an <code>icon</code> prop instead of placing icon elements as inline children.</p>
    <div class="cmp-row">
      <div class="cmp-cell"><h4 style="color:var(--red);">pf-codemods — ❌ Not addressed</h4></div>
      <div class="cmp-cell">
        <h4 style="color:var(--green);">semver/goose — ✅ Migrated (1 file)</h4>
        <pre><code>// ClusterUDNNamespaceSelector.tsx - Before:
&lt;ListItem&gt;&lt;ResourceIcon .../&gt; {name}&lt;/ListItem&gt;

// After:
&lt;ListItem icon={&lt;ResourceIcon .../&gt;}&gt;{name}&lt;/ListItem&gt;</code></pre>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</details>

<!-- --- StackItem --- -->
<details id="stackitem">
  <summary>6.12 StackItem Migration <span class="badge badge-red">Bug in semver/goose</span></summary>
  <div class="detail-body">
    <h4>What changed in PF6</h4>
    <p>The <code>StackItem</code> component's <code>component</code> prop specifies the HTML element type to render (e.g., <code>"div"</code>, <code>"span"</code>). It does <strong>not</strong> accept content/children.</p>

    <div class="cmp-row">
      <div class="cmp-cell">
        <h4>pf-codemods — No change (uses main's pattern)</h4>
        <pre><code>// Main pattern (correct PF6 usage):
&lt;StackItem&gt;{error?.message}&lt;/StackItem&gt;
&lt;StackItem&gt;&lt;Skeleton fontSize="lg" /&gt;&lt;/StackItem&gt;</code></pre>
        <p>Children are correctly placed as children of StackItem.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="cmp-cell">
        <h4 style="color:var(--red);">semver/goose — ❌ INCORRECT migration</h4>
        <pre><code>// ErrorAlert.tsx - WRONG:
&lt;StackItem component={error?.message} /&gt;
// 'component' expects ElementType ('div','span',etc.)
// NOT a string value like "Something went wrong"

// ListSkeleton.tsx - WRONG:
&lt;StackItem component={&lt;Skeleton fontSize="lg" /&gt;} /&gt;
// 'component' expects ElementType, NOT JSX element</code></pre>
        <p style="color:var(--red);"><strong>🔴 Will cause runtime errors.</strong> React will attempt to render the error message string as an HTML tag name (e.g., <code>&lt;Something went wrong&gt;</code>) or crash when receiving JSX where a string is expected.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p><strong>Verdict:</strong> The main branch's StackItem usage was already correct for PF6. semver/goose introduced bugs where none existed. <span class="badge badge-red">semver/goose penalized</span></p>
  </div>
</details>

